            <bioghist>
                <p>The J. H. Clay Company and the Ridgeway Brass Foundry were local manufacturers of
                    brass fittings and couplers used primarily in the fire fighting equipment
                    industry.</p>
            </bioghist>

            <scopecontent>
                <p>This is a collection of records related to the J.H. Clay Company. Records include
                    daybooks, ledgers, bills and receipts. The ledgers include enumerated personal,
                    shop, foundry, and house expenses. There are also several printed company
                    catalogs. Additionally the collection include roughly 500 letters, in German and
                    Polish, from Germany, Yugoslavia, Hungary, Austria, Argentina, and other
                    countries, dating from the 1930s to the 1950s. Most are addressed to John
                    Bogschutz or Theresa Seidl. John and Joseph Bogshutz ran the foundry. </p>
            </scopecontent>

